                    "description": "My action-research project 'Mapping Madaniya' aims at mapping the diverse (political, legal, religious, cultural, and artistic) notions, usages, and drivers of the Arabic concept of 'madaniya'. Together with students from different MENA countries, we hope to amplify voices of the MENA youth and intellectuals who - in the past as well as today - show us possible ways out of the vicious cycle of violence, gross injustices, forced migration, failed interventions, etc. This project also aims at filling the knowledge gap that exists in many political and security analyses on the MENA region, with locally produced knowledge in various formats. The focus of this pilot is on Iraq, Yemen and Jordan.",
